{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ff35974e-e92d-4e3f-a087-6efa6d3a08a3","content":"Use MAUI's `#if` platform directives combined with the standard DI container in `CreateMauiApp()`:\n\n```csharp\n// MauiProgram.cs\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.iOSNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\nEach implementation lives under its respective `Platforms/` folder (e.g., `Platforms/Android/AndroidNotificationService.cs`), which is already conditionally compiled per-platform by the default `.csproj` settings. This ensures only the relevant implementation is compiled and registered, so it won't break on any platform.\n\nThen inject it normally:\n\n```csharp\npublic MyViewModel(INotificationService notifications) { ... }\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c18f30b5-99c3-419a-9aff-191a5b8dba2b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` interface in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":365},"id":"fce49364-6abe-40d8-af60-748a7640c45d","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:40:43.093Z","parentId":"bd350dd9-d4af-456e-bc35-1f92eb9cc137"}
